<article>
    <h1>BASILICO&#x2019;S BEST OF THE BEST</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200717/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-07-17"><time>2020-07-17</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE | HAPPENINGS</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Re­gent Sin­ga­pore’s Basilico restau­rant, known for its Ital­ian cui­sine, marks its 12th an­niver­sary on July 24.</p>
    <p>To cel­e­brate, it is offering its best­sellers – one from each year – with a Best of the Best menu put to­gether by ex­ec­u­tive chef An­gelo Cic­cone. It is priced at $65++ (lunch) or $80++ (din­ner) with a choice of main course.</p>
    <p>High­lights in­clude the must-have three-cheese Nor­cia truf­fle mas­car­pone fo­cac­cia (right) from 2011; a seafood-filled Risotto alla Puglia with lob­ster, king scal­lop and tiger prawns from 2009; and this year’s star – tender char-grilled oc­to­pus with potato, hari­cot beans, dat­terino toma­toes and Lig­urian basil pesto.</p>
    <p>On July 24, the cel­e­bra­tions cul­mi­nate in a spe­cial four-course Puglia din­ner with wine pair­ings ($98++, 6.30 to 9.30pm), fea­tur­ing spe­cial­i­ties of Italy’s Sa­lento penin­sula – Gal­lipoli red prawns, salted an­chovies and orec­chi­ette pasta with broc­coli rabe.</p>
    <p>WHERE: Basilico, Level 2 Re­gent Sin­ga­pore, 1 Cus­ca­den Road</p>
    <p>MRT: Or­chard WHEN: Till July 24, noon to 2.30pm (week­days), noon to 3pm (week­ends), 6 to 9.30pm daily</p>
    <p>TEL: 6725-3232 INFO: E-mail basilico@re­gentsin­ga­pore.com.sg</p>

